  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6809 sitting 63 points below the GEX flip at 6872, dealers are currently long gamma and will mechanically buy any dips toward the 6755 negative gamma pocket while selling strength into the massive 5.3B positive gamma wall at 6900. The PIN regime combined with this heavy positive gamma skew above current levels creates a strong gravitational pull toward the 6850-6875 zone where dealers have over 6.8B in combined positive exposure. The 77% and 106% GEX surge over 1-5 minutes indicates rapid options flow that's building these stabilizing forces, making any move above 6872 likely to face immediate dealer selling pressure.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled toward 6850-6875 with dealers capping upside near 6900.",
